8 An Act relating to sales tax; requiring businesses to
obtain a permit to utilize the sale for resale sales
9 tax exemption; requiring the Oklahoma Tax Commission
to issue permit upon certain verification;
10 authorizing the Commission to issue permits by
electronic or other means; requiring vendors to honor
11 permit for exemption; prohibiting certain vendors
from claiming exemption without permit; providing for
12 misdemeanor if a person claims an exemption without a
permit; prescribing fine; providing for expiration of
13 permits; authorizing sellers to use system of
verification upon development; requiring the
14 Commission to verify validity of permit numbers;
requiring presumption of validity upon certain
15 verification; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1364.4 of Title 68, unless there
21 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. To utilize the sale for resale sales tax exemption, a
23 separate sale for resale exemption permit for each business to be
24 operated must be obtained from the Oklahoma Tax Commission. The
