1 perm it may be obtained at no charge. The Oklahoma Tax Commission
2 shall grant and issue to each applicant a sale for resale permit for
3 each business in this state, upon proper application therefor and
4 verification thereof by the Oklahoma Tax Commission. A business
5 with multiple locations in this state may operate under one sale for
6 resale permit. The Oklahoma Tax Commission may additionally provide
7 for the access to a granted and issued permit electronically, or by
8 other means as established by the Oklahoma Tax Commission.
9 B. All vendors shall honor a valid sale for resale permit for
10 the sales tax exemption authorized under this section and may
11 utilize the verification procedures outlined in subsection E of this
12 section. Sales to a person providing proof of such permit shall be
13 exempt from the tax levied by Section 1350 et seq. of Title 68 of
14 the Oklahoma Statutes.
15 C. It shall be unlawful for any person designated as a Group
16 One, Group Two, Group Three or Group Four vendor, pursuant to
17 Section 1363 of Title 68 of the Oklahoma Statutes, to claim a sale
18 for resale exemption within this state unless a sale for resale
19 permit or permits have been issued to such person. Any person who
20 claims a sale for resale exemption pursuant to the provisions of
21 this section without a sale for resale permit or permits, or after a
22 sale for resale permit has been suspended, upon conviction, shall be
23 guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by a fine not more than One
24 Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00).
